The distribution consists of configuration and resource packages to be
installed on top of Debian. While the preferred way to install the
system is via a live ISO, the packages can be added on top of an
existing Debian installation.

## Defining features

* Pre-configured [Openbox](http://openbox.org/wiki/Main_Page)-based
  desktop with a [tint2](https://gitlab.com/o9000/tint2) panel and
  [conky](http://conky.sourceforge.net/) system monitor
* Assortment of harmonising GTK2/3 themes, wallpapers and conky
  configurations
* Desktop-oriented configuration and helper utilities

